the difficulty of dealing in a dramatic way with what had been in prevocal days the pièce de résistance of comic shorts — the getting-unexpectedly-wet stunt. The hawkman in the toilet lounge pointed out (between cigar and cuspidor) that the difficulty might be neatly countered by showing only her shadow, her falling shadow, falling and glancing across the edge of the turfy bank amid a shower of shadowy flowers. See? Then: a garland afloat. That puritanical leather (on which they sat) was the